<h1 class="page-header">Getting Started</h1>

<p class="lead">We are working towards making it easier to get started with this starter kit everyday.</p> 

<p>The kit is still in beta stage, please follow the steps below to setup the project:</p>

<ol>
	<li>If you do not have a <strong>Heroku</strong> account, go to <a href="https://heroku.com/" target="_blank">Heroku</a> to sign up for an account.</li>
	<li>Once you have created an account (or if you already have an existing Heroku account), go to <a href="https://toolbelt.heroku.com/" target="_blank">Heroku Toolbelt</a> to download the program and follow the installation steps.</li>
	<li>Open up your console (for OS X - terminal.app, for Windows - command prompt) and type <code>heroku login</code> to login with your account.</li>
	<li>Create a Heroku app by typing <code>heroku create &lt;app-name-in-alphanumeric-without-space&gt;</code>.</li>
	<li>Clone StarterKit by typing <code>git clone git@github.com:starterkit-io/starterkit.git &lt;app-name-in-alphanumeric-without-space&gt;</code>.
	</li>
	<li>After the cloning process is done, change directory to the project folder by typing <code>cd &lt;app-name-in-alphanumeric-without-space&gt;</code>.</li>
	<li>Once you are in the project folder, add heroku to your project by typing <code>git remote add heroku https://git.heroku.com/&lt;app-name-in-alphanumeric-without-space&gt;.git</code>.</li>
	<li>Next, you need to add <a href="https://www.heroku.com/postgres" target="_blank">Heroku Postgre</a> to your heroku app. To do this, type <code>heroku addons:create heroku-postgresql:hobby-dev</code>.</li>
	<li>Then, you will need to do the same for <a href="https://elements.heroku.com/addons/heroku-redis" target="_blank">Heroku Redis</a>. Type <code>heroku addons:create heroku-redis:hobby-dev</code>.</li>
	<li>As the starterkit pre-built with all the user authentication features such as forget password, it is tightly coupled with an email service and for our choice, we chose <a href="https://sparkpost.com">SparkPost</a>. To add SparkPost, type <code>heroku addons:create sparkpost:free</code>.</li>
	<li>This starterkit is also equiped with the finest NodeJS monitoring service, <a href="https://trace.risingstack.com/" target="_blank">Trace by RisingStack</a>. To enable it, we need to type <code>heroku addons:create trace:lite</code>.</li>
	<li><span class="label label-warning">OPTIONAL</span> <a href="https://liberato.com" target="_blank">Liberato</a> provides a nice dashboard on the Heroku services that will be handy for monitoring at a glance. You can enable it for free via <code>heroku addons:create librato:development</code>.</li>
	<li><span class="label label-warning">OPTIONAL</span> <a href="https://logdna.com" target="_blank">LogDNA</a> is an excellent cloud log management system where you can do a live tail on the processes. You can enable it for free via <code>heroku addons:create logdna:quaco</code>.</li>
	<li>Finally, you deploy the starterkit by typing <code>git push heroku master</code>.</li>
	<li>Once the deployment is done, you can type <code>http://&lt;app-name-in-alphanumeric-without-space&gt;.herokuapp.com</code> into your browser to see your shiny new application.</li>
</ol>

<br/>

<h4>Done. Easy peasy.</h4>
